Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_proc_verbose(25.10)                                set_proc_verbose(25.10)

Name
       set_proc_verbose  -  Makes  a  procedure verbose, when the procedure is
       called for execution

Syntax
       set_proc_verbose

       [-help]

       {[<procedure_name> [-quiet ]] | [-report ]}

       Makes a procedure verbose, when the procedure is called for execution.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each set_proc_verbose parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man set_proc_verbose.

       <procedure_name>
              Specifies the name of the procedure to be made verbose.

              Data_type: string, required

       -quiet Reverts the procedure back from being verbose.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -report
              Reports procedures that are verbose.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
              *

                The  following commands show the usage of the set_proc_verbose
                command and its options for the fplan_boxes procedure.

                The code within the fplan_boxes procedure is given below:

                innovus 1> proc fplan_boxes {} {

                + puts "Floor Plan Boxes:"

                + puts [dbGet top.fplan.boxes]

                + }

                The following  command  executes  the  fplan_boxes  procedure.
                Please note that the execution result simply shows the coordi-
                nates of the floor plan boxes.

                innovus 2> fplan_boxes

                Floor Plan Boxes:

                {{0.0 0.0 1511.96 1512.12}}

                The  following  commands  makes the fplan_boxes procedure ver-
                bose:

                innovus 3> set_proc_verbose fplan_boxes

                fplan_boxes

                After the fplan_boxes procedure is made verbose  and  is  exe-
                cuted, the code of the fplan_boxes procedure is displayed:

                innovus 5> fplan_boxes

                #@ Begin verbose proc fplan_boxes

                @proc(fplan_boxes) 1: puts "Floor Plan Boxes:"

                Floor Plan Boxes:

                @proc(fplan_boxes) 2: dbGet top.fplan.boxes

                @proc(fplan_boxes) 3: puts [dbGet top.fplan.boxes]

                {{0.0 0.0 1511.96 1512.12}}

                #@ End verbose proc fplan_boxes

                You can use the -report option to see the verbose procedures:

                innovus 7> set_proc_verbose -report

                innovus 8> fplan_boxes

                If  you  have  made your procedure verbose and now you want to
                make it non-verbose, you can use the -quite option.  The  com-
                mand below makes the fplan_boxes procedure non-verbose:

                innovus 6> set_proc_verbose fplan_boxes -quiet

                fplan_boxes

